# Colocate Component Props

Define component-specific props interfaces in the same file as the component.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD – props beside component
// Chart.tsx
export interface ChartProps {
  data: ChartData
  options?: ChartOptions
  style?: React.CSSProperties
}

const ChartComponent = ({ data, options, style }: ChartProps) => { ... }
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD – props in central types when only one component uses them
// types.ts
export interface ChartProps { ... }

// Chart.tsx
import type { ChartProps } from './types'
```

- Keep shared types (`ChartData`, `ChartOptions`, etc.) in central type files
- Only component-specific `*Props` interfaces live beside the component
- **Place the `*Props` interface at the top of the file**, same page as the component (before or right after imports)
